From: Fugang Duan <b38611@freescale.com>
Date: Wed, 25 Mar 2015 10:29:33 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 0024/1691] MLK-10474 net: fec: remove frag number check

commit 750090f3b526d74a9b3fded25a75837de1a94c3c from
git://git.freescale.com/imx/linux-2.6-imx.git imx_4.1.15_1.0.0_ga

Since TSO has no frag list, the frag number is zero. Remove the frag number
check to fix kernel dump issue when SW TSO feature enable.

Signed-off-by: Fugang Duan <B38611@freescale.com>
(cherry picked from commit: 670cd419ffa15bbe967c6e11d9435faadd6790f3)
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fec_main.c | 3 +--
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fec_main.c b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fec_main.c
index 6178620..233c831 100644
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fec_main.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fec_main.c
@@ -1234,8 +1234,7 @@ fec_enet_tx_queue(struct net_device *ndev, u16 queue_id)
 			skb = txq->tx_skbuff[index];
 			bdnum++;
 		}
-		if (skb_shinfo(skb)->nr_frags &&
-		    (status = bdp_t->cbd_sc) & BD_ENET_TX_READY)
+		if ((status = bdp_t->cbd_sc) & BD_ENET_TX_READY)
 			break;
 
 		for (i = 0; i < bdnum; i++) {
